  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3782" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>23 Hostel Central, Biarritz, B. P. Frankreich. 27 December, 1901. </dateline>
        <opener>Dear D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi> H. Schuchardt, </opener>
        <p>I have already sent you a postcard today touching my definition of <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">cituán</hi> in Leiçarragas version of the Gospels of S<hi
            rendition="#sup">t</hi> Mark and S<hi rendition="#sup">t</hi>. Luke. I send also the number of <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Notes and Queries</hi> for the 14<hi
            rendition="#sup">th</hi> of this month, because it contains the list of my works on Baskish hitherto published. You must remember that my <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">synopsis</hi> of the Leiçarragan Verb, <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">if it were published as a whole</hi>, <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">would supply a need felt by all who study that language.</hi> It is easier to criticize it than to make it. <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">It consumes an immense amount of time</hi>; <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">it costs much to print </hi>it; <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">&amp; few persons buy it when it is published.</hi> My reprint of Leiçarragas New Testament will, I hope, <hi
            rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">be free from the defects which are to be found in yours.</hi> It will, probably, be finished in 1903. The Clarendon Press in Oxford will produce it, at the cost of the Trinitarian Bible Society in London. It will be <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">very small</hi>, and printed <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">page for page from your edition</hi>, <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">on beautiful</hi>, <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">thin</hi>, <hi rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">tough</hi>, <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">paper</hi>. I have leave to <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">partly</hi> modernise the spelling, &amp; hope to obtain leave to do so <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">completely</hi>. This will differentiate the edition from yours. I hope you will live to see it.</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Yours truly</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1402">E. S. Dodgson</persName>. </signed>
        </closer>
        <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
      </div>
    </body>
